This paper deals with a machine learning problem in the context of dynamic pricing, which involves optimizing prices over time based on demand data. This falls under the category of machine learning (cs.LG) and game theory (cs.GT), as well as artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and data structures (cs.DS) due to the algorithmic and computational aspects of the problem. Additionally, the paper discusses the statistical properties of the offline data, which relates to the field of econometrics (cs.EC).
